 `H ≤ K` are\nsubgroups, then `H` as a subgroup of `K` is isomorphic, as a topological group, to `H` as a subgroup\nof `G`. This is `addSubgroupOfEquivOfLe` upgraded to a `ContinuousAddEquiv`.","docLink":"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/IsUniformGroup/DiscreteSubgroup.html#AddSubgroup.addSubgroupOfContinuousAddEquivOfLe","kind":"def","line":30,"name":"AddSubgroup.addSubgroupOfContinuousAddEquivOfLe","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/IsUniformGroup/DiscreteSubgroup.lean#L30-L32"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Algebra/IsUniformGroup/DiscreteSubgroup.html#Subgroup.subgroupOfContinuousMulEquivOfLe\"><span class=\"name\">Subgroup</span>.<span class=\"name\">subgroupOfContinuousMulEquivOfLe</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">G</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Defs.html#Group\">Group</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">[<span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#TopologicalSpace\">TopologicalSpace</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>]</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">H </span><span class=\"fn\">K</span> : <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Algebra/Group/Subgroup/Defs.html#Subgroup\">Subgroup</a> <span class=\"fn\">G</span></span>}</span></span>\n</span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">hHK</span> : <span class=\"fn\">H</span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#LE.le\">≤</a> <span cl